### ğŸ‘‰ **Goal:**

Hard disk ko zero overwrite karke data remove karna, phir recovery try karke prove karna ke data recover nahi hota.

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-1: Identify External Disk**

```bash
lsblk
```

ğŸ“Œ Isse pata chalega external disk ka name kya hai
Example â†’ `/dev/sdb`

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-2: Zeroization (Complete Disk Wipe)**

```bash
sudo dd if=/dev/zero of=/dev/sdb bs=4M status=progress
```

ğŸ“Œ Ye pura disk zeros se overwrite karega
ğŸ“Œ Isme time lag sakta hai (disk size par depend karta hai)

âš ï¸ **Sahi disk name use karna â€” galat hua toh system wipe ho jayega**

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-3: Verify Disk is Zero**

```bash
sudo xxd /dev/sdb | head
```

ğŸ“Œ Output mostly `00 00 00 ...` hoga
ğŸ“Œ Ye proof hai ke disk empty & zeroized hai

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-4: Partition Create (gdisk)**

```bash
sudo gdisk /dev/sdb
```

Inside gdisk:

```
o   (create new GPT table)
y
n   (new partition)
enter
enter
enter
w   (write)
y
```

Done â†’ exit

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-5: Format Partition to EXT4**

```bash
sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdb1
```

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-6: Mount Partition**

```bash
sudo mkdir /mnt/data
sudo mount /dev/sdb1 /mnt/data
```

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-7: Create Test File (optional check)**

```bash
sudo cp /usr/share/pixmaps/debian-logo.png /mnt/data/test.png
ls /mnt/data
```

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-8: Delete File**

```bash
sudo rm /mnt/data/test.png
ls /mnt/data
```

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-9: Install Foremost Tool**

```bash
sudo apt install foremost -y
```

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-10: Recovery Folder Create**

```bash
sudo mkdir /home/recovery
sudo chmod 777 /home/recovery
```

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-11: File Recovery Attempt**

```bash
sudo foremost -i /dev/sdb1 -t all -o /home/recovery -v
```

---

## **âœ¨ STEP-12: Check Recovery Result**

```bash
cd /home/recovery
ls
```

ğŸ“Œ Mostly **recovery folder empty hoga**
ğŸ“Œ Proof: **Zeroization success**

